⠀
“It was football that built me,” says Ferhat Ciçek, director of Paris Alésia Football Club.
⠀
Ferhat wants the sport to do the same for the kids in his community in Paris’s 14th arrondissement. Since taking over in 2014, when @paris_alesia_fc had 80 kids, Ferhat has grown the club substantially. It now has over 750 players and last season, started a girls’ program.
⠀
“Here we have a big stadium that can welcome a lot of different people,” Ferhat says. “Here is a football club for all the levels. Here is a place where you meet people. Here the language that is spoken is football.”
⠀
Filmed in December 2019, watch Episode 3 of our series, “From the Grounds Up,” about the people creating community change through football on IGTV or read more at the link below. 
⠀
📖:https://go.nike.com/tRNW15MryFK
⠀

⠀
“They're not just playing football together, they're trying to build more common ground.”
⠀
That’s the mission of Abdulmalik Abdurahman, the founder of @fitzroylionssc, a youth football club in Melbourne, Australia. The club and its players have become a unifying force for their community.
⠀
With a shared goal to provide access to sport for girls and boys, Nike has partnered with the Lions since the start of their 2018 season to provide support through funding, training and game day kit and boots.
⠀
Filmed in December 2019 in Melbourne, Australia, watch Episode 2 of our series, “From the Grounds Up,” about football’s local heroes, on IGTV.
⠀

“I wanted to keep the kids off the streets, keep them occupied, and give them a path,” Bobby says. So he gave his community something it never had before: its own football club.
⠀
Bobby founded Hackney Wick FC with the help and support of Hackney’s residents. The club has grown from one men’s team, to nearly two dozen teams for men, women and youth in less than five years. The club played its first-ever FA Cup game last season.
⠀
“Football is my passion, it’s my world,” says Bobby. “And we’ve only been going for four years. What more can we achieve? What more can we produce? What other players can we have here?”
⠀
Watch Episode 1 of our new series, “From the Grounds Up,” about the people creating community change through football on IGTV.
⠀
#nikefootball #nikesoccer #nike #football #soccer

⠀
⠀
“We waited all our lives for the stadium to be full.”
- @andressaalves9oficial ⠀ ⠀ ⠀

Support for women’s football has grown globally—and significantly—in the months following last summer’s tournament, which was broadcast for the first time on national television in Brazil. The result? On November 16, 2019, @corinthiansfutebolfeminino set a record attendance for women’s club football in Brazil when they played in the men’s stadium— a first for the team.
⠀
For players like @adrianasilvaoficial_016, and the young girls in São Paulo and across the globe, last summer’s tournament marked a turning point for women’s football. The challenge now, Adriana says, is to keep the momentum going.
⠀
“You can't ever give up because the willpower is what leads to change, it’s what's going to break all barriers.”

“Who you are doesn’t matter when you’re on the pitch. That is what’s truly amazing about sports.” 

For Japanese soccer player Shiho Shimoyamada, she sees sport as a means to level the playing field. Regardless of gender, identity, or orientation, everyone should have a place to play.

Makeup: @marinoasahi
Hair: Miho Emori @miho_emo_

For young legend @tekkerzkid, the Land of New Football isn't just a place to play. It is a place to CREATE. 

New moves, new teams, new tricks, new celebrations, new whatever you can imagine. 

So what’s your new thing?

node.text:
In a world where success is often measured by individual achievement, @cristiano doesn’t lose sight of the impact he can have on those around him. “I strongly believe that one of the greatest impacts I can have as an athlete is to encourage people across the world” he says, before elaborating that he aspires for us all “to be positive as individuals both on the field and off the field.”

It’s the drive and desire to be a good influence that has led him to partnering with us to create his newest boot, CR7’s Mercurial Superfly “Spark Positivity” ⚡🎇

As he begins another journey to success on the international stage, he’s clear-headed with the following, “I truly want kids to be inspired by this boot and really chase their dreams, the same way I continue to chase my own each and every day.”

Available in select cities and retailers on 6/28 💥
